# SignalPilot Core Rules

## Architecture
- All data models are in `src/signalpilot/models.py` (pydantic v2)
- `Evidence = Annotated[Union[Signal, LogCluster, GitChange], Field(discriminator="type")]` — always use discriminated union
- Collectors are in `src/signalpilot/collectors/` — all implement `BaseCollector` with `is_available()` + `collect()`
- RCA rules are pure functions in `rca/rules.py` with signature `rule_fn(ctx: RcaContext) -> list[Finding]`
- The engine in `rca/engine.py` wraps every rule in try/except — rules must never crash the engine
- `get_settings()` is `@lru_cache(maxsize=1)` — call `.cache_clear()` in tests using `monkeypatch.setenv`

## Python conventions
- Python 3.12+, strict typing everywhere
- Pydantic v2: use `model_copy(update={...})` not `.copy()`
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` for forward refs
- `Signal.type = "signal"` (discriminator), never omit
- All collectors handle exceptions gracefully and return `[]` on failure
- `redact_secrets()` must be applied to all log text before storage

## Testing
- Unit tests use JSON fixtures in `tests/fixtures/k8s/` — no live cluster
- E2E tests in `tests/e2e/` skip automatically if no cluster available
- Signal fixtures always include `type="signal"` field
- Use `freezegun` for time-sensitive tests

## K8s compatibility
- Target K3s v1.22+ (rancher-desktop)
- Use `core/v1` events API (not `events.k8s.io/v1`)
- Crashloop detection: check BOTH `state.waiting.reason == "CrashLoopBackOff"` AND `restart_count >= 3` with `last_state.terminated.reason != OOMKilled` (pod briefly re-runs between crashes)
- Metrics-server: use `CustomObjectsApi` for `apis/metrics.k8s.io/v1beta1`

## File structure
- `src/signalpilot/` — source package (src layout)
- `tests/unit/` — fast fixture-based unit tests
- `tests/e2e/` — live cluster E2E tests
- `tests/fixtures/k8s/` — recorded K8s API JSON responses
- `deploy/samples/` — scenario manifests for `signalpilot-test` namespace (01–16)
- `scripts/` — capture_all_evidence.sh, reset_scenarios.sh, audit_evidence.py
- `evidence/` — HTML reports + JSON dumps (gitignored except README.md)
- `.signalpilot/` — runtime data dir (analyses, timelines, verifications)

## Evidence campaign (live testing)
- 16 scenario manifests in `deploy/samples/` cover: crash, OOM, imagepull, probe, unschedulable, regression, DNS, slow-transaction, memory-leak, cascading, configmap-missing, init-container-fail, latency-prometheus, git-correlation
- All manifests use ConfigMap-backed scripts (no inline commands) for reliability
- `bash scripts/reset_scenarios.sh` — redeploy all; `bash scripts/capture_all_evidence.sh` — capture 12 evidence sets
- `python3.12 scripts/audit_evidence.py` — verifies quality bar (conf ≥ 75%, ev ≥ 2, kubectl fix)

## RCA rules (as of 2026-06-13)
- 11 rules in `ALL_RULES`: oom_killed, cpu_throttled, crash_loop, image_pull_error, probe_failure, pending_unschedulable, code_regression, network_latency, configmap_error, init_container_fail, latency_spike
- New rule pattern: signal → evidence list → Finding (always add ≥ 2 corroborating signals)
- `rule_configmap_error`: fires on EVENT signals containing "CreateContainerConfigError"/"configmap"/"couldn't find key"
- `rule_init_container_fail`: fires on CRASH_LOOP signals with "[init:fail]" marker (emitted by KubeApiCollector for failed init containers)
- `rule_latency_spike`: fires on log clusters with is_new=True and slow/warn/p95 keywords

## Log clustering
- `is_new = cb == 0 and ca > 0` AND template matches ERROR_PATTERN OR latency keywords
- Log decode: `api.read_namespaced_pod_log()` may return `bytes` or `b"..."` repr strings — always pass through `_decode_log()` in `logs.py`
- Insecure fallback: if kubelet cert mismatch (x509), retry with `verify_ssl=False` — safe for local clusters

## HTML Report Design (2026-06-13)
- Template: `src/signalpilot/report/templates/report.html.j2` — self-contained, PerfSage branded
- Generator: `src/signalpilot/report/html.py` — adds `source_label`, `kind_label`, `kind_icon`, `severity_css`, `pct` Jinja2 filters
- Design: warm off-white bg `#F4F1ED`, deep navy header `#0D1F3C`, white cards, color-coded left borders per severity
- Template sections: header+severity pills → alert banner (top finding) → 5 KPI cards → narrative → deploy change → finding cards (collapsible, two-column fixes|evidence)
- Evidence rendering: type-discriminated (`signal`/`log_cluster`/`git_change`) — no raw Python enum values leak through
- Logo: embedded as base64 data URI via `_logo_data_uri()` (looks in workspace `.cursor/projects/.../assets/`)
- Regenerate reports: `python3.12 -c "from pathlib import Path; from signalpilot.models import Analysis; from signalpilot.report.html import generate_html_report; [generate_html_report(Analysis.model_validate_json(f.read_text()), f.parent/(f.stem.replace('_analysis','_report')+'.html')) for f in Path('evidence').glob('*_analysis.json')]"`

## K8s compatibility (additions)
- Init container failure: detected via `pod.status.init_container_statuses[*].state.waiting.reason == "CrashLoopBackOff"` or `last_state.terminated.exit_code != 0`; emitted as CRASH_LOOP with "[init:fail]" in message
- Pending pods: also emit NODE_CONDITION signal with CPU/mem resource requests for evidence corroboration
- Rancher Desktop kubelet cert fix: delete `/var/lib/rancher/k3s/agent/serving-kubelet.crt`, set `ADDITIONAL_ARGS="--node-ip=<internal-ip>"` in `/etc/conf.d/k3s`, restart k3s via `rc-service k3s restart`
